m and the same Nexus push release snap-buckle. Good to know that 100% feel gravel riding requires just as much head coverage as mountain biking.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers.jpg\" alt=\"100% altis gravel helmet smartshock rotational impact protection elastomers\" width=\"1600\" height=\"837\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-297x155.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-800x419.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-120x63.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-768x402.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-1536x804.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-297x155.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-800x419.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-120x63.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-768x402.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131754/100-altis-gravel-helmet-smartshock-elastomers-1536x804.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Losing the peak will make it a little lighter, and gives it a more gravel-appropriate aesthetic for those who care. Without it, you’ll be needing your sunglasses to keep the sun out of your eyes. When the weather is overcast the 100% Altis Gravel can stow your eyewear at the rear. Inside the helmet you’ll find a washable, moisture-wicking anti-microbial liner.</p><div id=\"attachment_271589\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131456/100-altis-gravel-helmet-sunglasses-stow.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271589\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131456/100-altis-gravel-helmet-sunglasses-stow.jpg\" alt=\"100% altis gravel helmet womens white red\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131456/100-altis-gravel-helmet-sunglasses-stow.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14131456/100-altis-gravel-helmet-